1
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:44,395
Listen to me.

2
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:47,356
OK, you win.

3
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:52,403
At least you could stop that song.
You know I hate it.

4
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:56,157
Why are you so quiet?

5
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:02,121
Say something!

6
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:22,493
You're there.

7
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:24,411
And you're looking at me.

8
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:27,790
Do you think you can fool me?

9
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:31,085
No, no, you can't fool me,

10
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:34,004
because I can feel your presence.

11
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:37,174
And your movements.

12
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,385
I can even smell you.

13
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:41,428
If you think...

14
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,014
If you think, son of a bitch,

15
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:46,850
that I'll hang myself
while you watch, you...

16
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,875
- What's wrong?
- What happened?

17
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:14,169
Julia, what's wrong?

18
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:17,381
Julia, can you hear me?
Bring some water.

19
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:19,258
Take it easy, Julia.

20
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,219
Julia, are you OK?

21
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,679
- What happened?
- She fell.

22
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:27,057
- Call a doctor, quick!
- No, I'm OK.

23
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,351
I'm OK.

24
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:38,360
This is Sara. I can't take your call
at the moment. Please...

25
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:44,325
Do you think it's a good idea
to show up after six months?

26
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:46,910
I just need to know
that she is all right.

27
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,414
Sara?

28
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:54,501
Sara?

29
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,881
Maybe they have gone out.

30
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:00,341
No...

31
00:05:00,508 --> 00:05:02,718
I know something's happened to her.

32
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:15,481
The power is out.

33
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:21,695
- The fuses seem to be OK.
- I'll look upstairs.

34
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:27,951
Sara?

35
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,295
Sara?

36
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:05,114
Isaac, she's nowhere to be found.
We'll ask the neighbors.

37
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,616
- Don't come down.
- Why?

38
00:06:10,537 --> 00:06:12,287
What's wrong?

39
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:17,960
Isaac, tell me what's wrong.

40
00:06:19,254 --> 00:06:21,046
- What's wrong?
- Julia...

41
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:23,549
- What's wrong?
- Come with me.

42
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,521
Inspector...

43
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:40,190
I'm sorry about what happened.

44
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,109
No, thanks.

45
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:46,905
The forensics say Sara took her own life
last night, during the blackout.

46
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:49,158
But we need to find out why.

47
00:06:49,325 --> 00:06:52,744
I have been informed that she suffered
a degenerative disease.

48
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:57,624
Yes, a progressive vision loss,
the same as my wife.

49
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:01,128
But Sara went blind a year ago.

50
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:03,464
And how did she cope with that?

51
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:07,676
My sister wasn't depressed,
if that's what you mean.

52
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:09,970
In fact, she was...

53
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:12,764
She was going to have surgery, right?

54
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:17,102
She was waiting for a donor,
but she hoped to get her vision back.

55
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:26,737
Maybe she got tired of waiting.

56
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:00,103
All right.

57
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:04,775
Yes, thank you.

58
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:12,533
Dr RomÃ¡n can't come to the funeral,
and he sends his condolences.

59
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:16,286
He also wants to check your eyes
before you go back home.

60
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:19,498
Isaac, the power is back.

61
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:24,086
Darling, are you listening?

62
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:27,172
And the CD started playing.
Did you hear it?

63
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,343
- Yes.
- Don't you think it's strange

64
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:34,596
that Sara was listening
to music before...?

65
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:37,057
Besides, she hated that song.

66
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:39,768
- Julia...
- What if she wasn't alone?

67
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:42,688
- What if she was with somebody?
- Julia, please.

68
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:47,067
We may never find out her reasons.
We hadn't heard from her in months.

69
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,695
It's strange.
I need to know what happened.

70
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:53,407
- It's not good for you to get upset.
- I'm not worried about myself.

71
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:57,953
Well, I am.
Stress can turn you blind.

72
00:08:58,121 --> 00:09:00,956
It's only happened to me
twice in five years.

73
00:09:01,124 --> 00:09:04,001
And you've lost 20% of your vision.

74
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:16,471
Oh, no... Again.

75
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:34,573
Did you find anything?

76
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:37,534
Nothing, not even a candle.

77
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,663
- It's time to meet the neighbors.
- OK, hurry up.

78
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,189
Isaac?

79
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,588
Julia.

80
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:06,456
Excuse me.

81
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:09,793
Excuse me.

82
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:17,968
I'm sorry for your loss.
I'm Blasco, her next-door neighbor.

83
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:20,929
I didn't know your sister very well,

84
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:26,143
but Lia loved her very much
and she wanted me to bring you this.

85
00:11:26,978 --> 00:11:28,019
Lia?

86
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:32,190
My daughter.
Sara used to lend her books.

87
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:37,487
The poor girl is so upset she didn't
want to come out of the car.

88
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:40,615
Anyway...

89
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:46,329
Sorry... Lia would like to know
if Sara left any note.

90
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:51,334
- We don't know.
- I understand.

91
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:55,130
Anyway, I won't bother you any longer.

92
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:03,096
Shall we continue?

93
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:05,557
Only a neighbor and his daughter?

94
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:10,479
I didn't know she was so lonely.

95
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:23,867
But I forgave her.

96
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:29,498
And I also forgave you.

97
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:38,215
Now I only need to forgive myself
for not being by her side.

98
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:50,477
But I did everything I could,
didn't I, Isaac?

99
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,621
The autopsy doesn't reveal
anything strange.

100
00:13:09,831 --> 00:13:14,543
- Have you searched for fingerprints?
- We only found ours and hers.

101
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,545
OK, but...

102
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:18,630
That song...

103
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,216
And what about what happened
in the cemetery?

104
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:26,179
Julia, there's no evidence
of anyone being with your sister.

105
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:29,724
And nobody has seen or heard
anything suspicious.

106
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:35,063
You can speak with Soledad if you wish.

107
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:38,316
- With whom?
- An old lady who lives nearby.

108
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:42,654
Apparently, she helped your sister
when she went blind.

109
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:45,282
Don't be long.

110
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:52,956
Where does she live?

111
00:13:53,124 --> 00:13:56,126
Follow the rope in the yard.

112
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,627
What rope?

113
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:12,309
I'm sure the old woman
doesn't know anything.

114
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:15,604
Nobody else knew apart from you.

115
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:20,567
But you have to speak with your wife.
She'll find out sooner or later.

116
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:24,279
I'll wait for the right moment.

117
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:55,560
Mrs Soledad?

118
00:15:02,193 --> 00:15:03,777
Hello?

119
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:08,531
Who is it?

120
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,659
It's Julia, Sara's sister.

121
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:12,494
I'll be right out.

122
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:22,295
Sorry about the mess.
The house must be quite disgusting.

123
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:26,883
Hello...

124
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:32,097
- Are you there?
- Yes. Sorry, I didn't know you were...

125
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:37,268
I am sorry too. I wanted to come
to your sister's funeral, but...

126
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,480
it took me an hour to find
a pair of matching shoes.

127
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:42,148
It's OK.

128
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:45,193
Were you a good friend of Sara?

129
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:49,155
Well, when she started
losing her eyesight,

130
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:54,202
a year ago,
we used to have long conversations.

131
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:59,749
But lately she hardly spoke with me.

132
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,252
She had made new friends.

133
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:06,840
- What new friends?
- You know, younger people.

134
00:16:07,008 --> 00:16:11,219
- From the Baumann Centre.
- Baumann Centre. What's that?

135
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:14,055
A centre for blind people,
not far from here.

136
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:20,437
One of those places where they make you
believe you can live a normal life.

137
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:25,275
If you can't hear, you are deaf.
If you lost an arm, you are a cripple.

138
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:28,236
And if you can't see, you are blind.

139
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:31,322
And nothing can ever be
how it used to be.

140
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:35,618
Mrs Soledad, where can I take a taxi?

141
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,454
Thank you.

142
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:45,795
Go straight ahead,
down the stairs and turn right.

143
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:09,027
Poor Sara.

144
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:12,530
- Why would she hang herself?
- Stop thinking about it.

145
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:15,492
- Shall we have a moment of silence?
- Don't be cruel.

146
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:18,369
None of us could stand her.

147
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:21,122
Don't you find it strange?

148
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,665
No.

149
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,876
We've all thought
of doing it at some time.

150
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:28,004
Dela...

151
00:17:28,214 --> 00:17:31,633
Nora is right. I once thought
of slitting my wrists.

152
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:35,178
With candles and opera music.

153
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:37,972
Me too, I thought of jumping
out of the window.

154
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:41,184
Well, we thought about it
but didn't do it.

155
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:44,354
There's a reason to live.

156
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,315
Maybe Sara didn't find any.

157
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:51,903
And a boyfriend doesn't seem like
a good reason?

158
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:54,280
Sara had a boyfriend?

159
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,407
She told me she met a boy.

160
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:58,618
- Who?
- No idea.

161
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:02,330
They had been going out together
for a couple of months.

162
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,750
They even went to Bellavista
together for a week.

163
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:10,922
- What's in Bellavista?
- Rooms for sex.

164
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:14,717
Quiet!

165
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,937
How weird! Shit!

166
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:27,772
What is it?

167
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:30,400
There's someone here.

168
00:18:30,568 --> 00:18:34,237
- I would say it's Sara.
- That's not funny!

169
00:18:34,697 --> 00:18:38,950
- I can smell her too.
- Something is moving.

170
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:43,496
- I've got her! Call security!
- I'm Sara's sister.

171
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:45,248
Julia?

172
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,292
Yes.

173
00:18:47,418 --> 00:18:51,504
- Why were you spying on us?
- I just didn't want to interrupt.

174
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:54,507
- And who is he?
- Who?

175
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:56,926
- The man who came with you.
- I came alone.

176
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:00,263
There's someone else here.

177
00:19:00,431 --> 00:19:03,224
A man, and he's right behind you.

178
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:24,662
Wait!

179
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,336
Who are you?

180
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:58,047
Turn around.

181
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,009
Turn around.

182
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,719
I said turn around!

183
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:41,674
No, no!

184
00:22:02,237 --> 00:22:03,946
Isaac?

185
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:11,829
Isaac?

186
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:30,973
Hotel Romeo, Bellavista.

187
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:35,144
What happened to you?

188
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:37,772
You are soaking wet.

189
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:40,691
It started raining
when I left Soledad's house.

190
00:22:41,652 --> 00:22:43,861
Have you been with her all this time?

191
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:48,491
She invited me for tea.
I couldn't say no.

192
00:22:48,659 --> 00:22:53,830
Julia, I went to look for you.
You left her place an hour ago.

193
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:56,541
Where have you been?

194
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,876
Why are you so controlling?

195
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,712
I could also ask you
what you're looking for.

196
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,509
Fine.

197
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:09,345
Fine.

198
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:13,182
Now I'm certain there was
something strange in Sara's suicide.

199
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:18,020
- There's someone watching us.
- Julia, Julia, please.

200
00:23:18,188 --> 00:23:19,480
Who?

201
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:24,652
Her boyfriend.

202
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:26,863
- Sara had a boyfriend?
- Yes.

203
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,030
Who told you?

204
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:30,575
A group of blind girls told me
at the Baumann Centre

205
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:32,535
and someone was spying on us.

206
00:23:32,703 --> 00:23:35,329
- How do you know?
- Because I ran after him.

207
00:23:35,456 --> 00:23:38,541
- You ran after him?
- Yes, I did.

208
00:23:38,876 --> 00:23:40,293
Isaac.

209
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:44,380
- Isaac! What are you doing?
- We're leaving this house.

210
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:48,134
Listen to me. If I have to be
a controlling husband, I will be.

211
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:50,511
And if I have to drag you out of here,
I will too.

212
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,473
But I won't let you have a seizure.

213
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,517
You know I would never
forgive myself.

214
00:23:56,977 --> 00:23:59,604
Your sister's death has hurt us enough.

215
00:24:07,696 --> 00:24:09,447
You're right.

216
00:24:10,908 --> 00:24:13,034
But I don't feel like
going back home.

217
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:17,413
Why don't we go somewhere,
you and me, alone?

218
00:24:27,591 --> 00:24:30,176
Where would you like to go?

219
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:59,038
- Are you sure you want to stay there?
- The guide says it's the coziest hotel.

220
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,174
Nice view, isn't it?

221
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:14,804
- Julia.
- Yes, yes. It's beautiful.

222
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:16,347
Thank you.

223
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:18,891
Julia...

224
00:25:19,101 --> 00:25:22,311
- I'll park the car.
- Yes, OK.

225
00:25:25,983 --> 00:25:28,526
You don't remember my sister,
a blind woman?

226
00:25:28,694 --> 00:25:31,362
Yes, a colleague talked to me about her.

227
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:33,114
This may sound weird,

228
00:25:33,282 --> 00:25:36,450
but could you find out
the name of the man who was with her?

229
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:41,330
- There's no name on the receipt.
- Sorry, but I don't remember any man.

230
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:42,665
The thing is...

231
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:45,751
my sister is dead,
and I need to find this man.

232
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:48,879
Let me see... I don't understand.

233
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,632
Her booking is not registered.

234
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:55,344
It's as if all the information
was deleted.

235
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:59,974
- Are you sure?
- Sorry. It must be a computer problem.

236
00:26:00,809 --> 00:26:05,646
You could try El Arlequin. It's the
restaurant we recommend to our guests.

237
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:07,315
Thank you.

238
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:08,524
Thank you.

239
00:26:15,782 --> 00:26:17,033
Thank you.

240
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:20,703
I don't understand how they can
recommend this restaurant.

241
00:26:20,871 --> 00:26:22,788
I like it.

242
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:27,835
It's not your style at all.

243
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:34,967
And that waiter
won't stop staring at you.

244
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:36,844
Really?

245
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:45,686
- It's your imagination.
- Maybe.

246
00:26:49,941 --> 00:26:54,028
- My reading glasses...
- In your coat? How weird.

247
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:58,699
I'll go and get them,
and I'll go to the toilet too.

248
00:27:00,577 --> 00:27:03,412
If he hits on you, just yell.

249
00:27:14,216 --> 00:27:16,133
What a change!

250
00:27:16,510 --> 00:27:21,347
I like it. It highlights your eyes.
By the way, I knew they were green.

251
00:27:22,182 --> 00:27:25,810
You're confusing me with my twin sister.
She was here last week.

252
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:27,937
With her boyfriend.

253
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,563
Her boyfriend?

254
00:27:29,731 --> 00:27:32,108
She came with a man, didn't she?

255
00:27:32,943 --> 00:27:35,194
Yes, I think so.

256
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:39,448
- Do you remember his name?
- No, no idea.

