519
00:52:21,597 --> 00:52:25,057
OK, Julia... Everything went well.

520
00:52:26,101 --> 00:52:28,603
But we have to be careful now.

521
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:33,024
You eyes must be protected
from the light for two weeks.

522
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:35,776
And don't manipulate
the bandages yourself.

523
00:52:35,944 --> 00:52:40,072
If you remove them too soon,
there won't be a solution.

524
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:43,743
But don't worry,
you will be taken care of.

525
00:52:44,286 --> 00:52:45,703
No.

526
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:48,789
I'd rather go home.
I hate hospitals.

527
00:52:48,957 --> 00:52:51,709
I know,
but I'm afraid that's impossible.

528
00:52:51,877 --> 00:52:56,756
- You need supervision.
- I could... go to my sister's house.

529
00:52:56,924 --> 00:52:59,634
I know my way around it very well.

530
00:53:01,470 --> 00:53:04,472
Julia, honestly,
I don't think it's a good idea.

531
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:08,434
Right, but if I can't see, I can't feel.

532
00:53:11,188 --> 00:53:15,566
All right, let's do this.
You can go to your sister's house.

533
00:53:15,734 --> 00:53:19,946
But a care worker will visit you
every day, OK?

534
00:53:25,452 --> 00:53:28,913
Julia, there's something else.

535
00:53:30,666 --> 00:53:34,168
Your husband's body is still here.
I can take care of it if you want.

536
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:36,128
No.

537
00:53:37,965 --> 00:53:40,841
I'd rather do it myself.

538
00:53:41,677 --> 00:53:45,179
Could you keep the body
until I can see again?

539
00:53:45,347 --> 00:53:48,182
I need to say goodbye to him.

540
00:53:58,944 --> 00:54:01,362
Let's sit on the sofa. Slowly.

541
00:54:01,530 --> 00:54:03,447
Keep walking...

542
00:54:03,824 --> 00:54:06,617
- Here are your things.
- Thank you.

543
00:54:08,036 --> 00:54:11,372
- Careful. Don't worry.
- No problem.

544
00:54:15,377 --> 00:54:18,296
Shall we wait here
until the care worker arrives?

545
00:54:18,463 --> 00:54:21,257
- Can you do me a favor?
- Sure. What is it?

546
00:54:21,425 --> 00:54:23,926
I'd like to know what this key opens.

547
00:54:35,397 --> 00:54:38,190
Whatever it is this key opens,
it's not here.

548
00:54:38,358 --> 00:54:41,569
- Did you try every lock?
- I did.

549
00:54:41,737 --> 00:54:44,071
Do you need anything else?

550
00:54:44,239 --> 00:54:45,948
No, thank you.

551
00:54:46,116 --> 00:54:48,743
- You can go.
- All right.

552
00:55:58,480 --> 00:56:00,481
- Hello?
- Hi.

553
00:56:00,649 --> 00:56:03,859
You must be Julia.
I'm IvÃ¡n, the care worker.

554
00:56:04,027 --> 00:56:07,988
Sorry I'm late. The traffic was bad.
I phoned you, but it got cut off.

555
00:56:11,243 --> 00:56:13,828
I would have preferred a woman.

556
00:56:16,248 --> 00:56:18,874
If you want to call Dr RomÃ¡n...
What happened to your hand?

557
00:56:22,838 --> 00:56:27,591
It's just a scratch. You won't
feel anything tomorrow morning.

558
00:56:28,635 --> 00:56:33,013
I will make you dinner
and clean up a bit. You stay here.

559
00:56:34,057 --> 00:56:35,641
By the way...

560
00:56:37,102 --> 00:56:40,062
What should I do with the glasses?

561
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:41,814
Throw them out.

562
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:49,572
While you ate,
I familiarized myself with the house.

563
00:56:50,532 --> 00:56:52,032
Julia.

564
00:56:55,203 --> 00:56:57,997
- What are you doing?
- Sorry. I have to go.

565
00:56:58,165 --> 00:56:59,999
What time is it?

566
00:57:00,125 --> 00:57:02,209
It's nine o'clock.

567
00:57:02,377 --> 00:57:04,837
On the first days,
we lose track of time.

568
00:57:06,047 --> 00:57:09,550
I'll give you a couple
of sleeping pills, just in case.

569
00:57:09,718 --> 00:57:12,595
And also a pager.

570
00:57:12,762 --> 00:57:16,557
If you want to contact me,
press this button. Give me your hand.

571
00:57:17,017 --> 00:57:19,810
Look, here's the button.

572
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:29,612
Let's go.

573
00:57:29,779 --> 00:57:32,573
- What are you doing?
- I have to put you to bed.

574
00:57:33,116 --> 00:57:36,994
- Sorry, but I can do it myself.
- Are you sure?

575
00:57:46,004 --> 00:57:47,755
Are you OK?

576
00:57:48,798 --> 00:57:51,258
OK, you win.

577
00:57:51,426 --> 00:57:53,511
Put me to bed and then you can go.

578
00:58:19,704 --> 00:58:21,372
Who's there?

579
00:58:25,794 --> 00:58:29,046
Calm down.
Calm down, darling.

580
00:58:30,131 --> 00:58:31,715
It's me.

581
00:58:31,883 --> 00:58:33,676
Isaac?

582
00:58:35,554 --> 00:58:36,762
Isaac?

583
00:58:37,806 --> 00:58:40,057
How can this be?

584
00:58:45,564 --> 00:58:48,107
Don't say anything.

585
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:51,193
Thank you.

586
00:58:52,654 --> 00:58:57,866
- What are you doing?
- Taking this dirty bandage off.

587
00:58:58,493 --> 00:59:01,537
- So you can see me better.
- No!

588
00:59:03,665 --> 00:59:05,374
That's it, that's it.

589
00:59:06,084 --> 00:59:09,503
Leave me alone.
Get off me! Get off me!

590
00:59:10,297 --> 00:59:15,759
Don't resist, little sister.
We're two against one.

591
00:59:20,599 --> 00:59:22,266
Don't move.

592
00:59:22,434 --> 00:59:24,435
No, stop!

593
00:59:26,730 --> 00:59:28,022
Get off me!

594
01:00:04,893 --> 01:00:06,727
IvÃ¡n. IvÃ¡n.

595
01:00:06,853 --> 01:00:09,063
Julia, is everything OK?

596
01:00:09,230 --> 01:00:12,900
- I think there's someone in the house.
- What?

597
01:00:13,068 --> 01:00:15,319
In the room next door.

598
01:00:15,737 --> 01:00:19,740
- Don't move. I'll call the police.
- No, IvÃ¡n, IvÃ¡n.

599
01:00:33,713 --> 01:00:35,881
Are you still there?

600
01:00:38,009 --> 01:00:40,928
You have to get me out of here
right now.

601
01:00:41,096 --> 01:00:44,431
- Where are you?
- In the guest room.

602
01:00:44,599 --> 01:00:47,351
That's good.
Find the door and get out of the room.

603
01:00:49,229 --> 01:00:51,814
Find the door to your right.

604
01:00:53,942 --> 01:00:55,484
- He's there.
- Calm down.

605
01:00:55,652 --> 01:00:58,487
The handrail is in front of you.
Look for it.

606
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:00,155
OK, yes.

607
01:01:00,323 --> 01:01:02,616
Hold onto the handrail.

608
01:01:02,784 --> 01:01:05,786
Go down the six steps
to the first landing.

609
01:01:09,874 --> 01:01:12,167
Then there's nine more.

610
01:01:14,629 --> 01:01:16,171
Julia...

611
01:01:17,298 --> 01:01:22,469
- I'm downstairs. What now?
- Follow the wall to the door.

612
01:01:29,811 --> 01:01:31,687
Who are you?
Who are you?

613
01:01:31,855 --> 01:01:33,647
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

614
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:36,483
Get out of the house! Quick!

615
01:01:53,042 --> 01:01:56,503
There is no indication
that someone entered the house.

616
01:01:56,671 --> 01:02:00,340
There was someone there.
And he was looking for something.

617
01:02:00,508 --> 01:02:04,011
Sorry, but there's nothing else
I can do.

618
01:02:07,849 --> 01:02:10,100
- Do you want me to call the hospital?
- Why?

619
01:02:10,268 --> 01:02:14,021
Maybe you shouldn't recover here,
considering what you've been through.

620
01:02:14,189 --> 01:02:16,023
You don't believe me either.

621
01:02:16,191 --> 01:02:21,653
I'm just saying that in your situation,
it's normal if your senses deceive you.

622
01:02:21,863 --> 01:02:25,032
Don't open your eyes now.

623
01:02:26,910 --> 01:02:28,952
You can let go now.

624
01:02:30,538 --> 01:02:32,372
What's the matter?

625
01:02:34,250 --> 01:02:36,251
My eyes could get damaged, right?

626
01:02:36,419 --> 01:02:41,215
No, I only want to change the bandage,
and I took precautions.

627
01:02:41,382 --> 01:02:44,468
I've done this a hundred times.
Don't worry.

628
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:51,642
You know, when I was 20 years old,

629
01:02:51,810 --> 01:02:54,895
I had a car accident
and I was blind for two months.

630
01:02:56,898 --> 01:03:02,903
And like you now,
I imagined things and had nightmares.

631
01:03:03,071 --> 01:03:05,531
And I rejected the care worker's help.

632
01:03:08,326 --> 01:03:10,911
I couldn't stand the idea
of going blind.

633
01:03:17,126 --> 01:03:19,586
In the end, I recovered my sight.

634
01:03:22,465 --> 01:03:25,092
But during those months...

635
01:03:26,344 --> 01:03:29,638
...I understood what it was like
to live in the dark.

636
01:03:33,560 --> 01:03:36,103
That's why I became a care worker.

637
01:03:37,272 --> 01:03:39,648
You made that up
to make me feel better.

638
01:03:39,816 --> 01:03:43,360
No, no. Call the hospital
if you don't believe me.

639
01:03:43,903 --> 01:03:49,533
Julia, I know you're scared,
but the only way to lose that fear

640
01:03:49,742 --> 01:03:51,618
is to fight it.

641
01:03:58,293 --> 01:04:00,210
What do you say?

642
01:04:02,630 --> 01:04:04,631
Will you let me help you?

643
01:04:14,100 --> 01:04:15,851
- What happened?
- You spilled it.

644
01:04:16,019 --> 01:04:19,730
Try to get to the door.
Follow the wall with your hand...

645
01:04:23,359 --> 01:04:25,485
And after the glass cabinet...

646
01:04:49,093 --> 01:04:52,679
Well, I have my ups and downs.

647
01:04:52,847 --> 01:04:55,098
But I slept very well
the last few nights.

648
01:04:55,266 --> 01:04:58,518
IvÃ¡n has been
very patient with me all week.

649
01:04:58,686 --> 01:05:00,729
Yes, he takes good care of me.

650
01:05:00,897 --> 01:05:04,024
I will. I will, yes.

651
01:05:04,192 --> 01:05:06,276
Thanks a lot for calling. Bye.

652
01:05:08,071 --> 01:05:11,657
- Are you leaving?
- Yes. It's a little late.

653
01:05:11,824 --> 01:05:13,867
Why don't stay a bit longer?

654
01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:17,204
A little while.

655
01:05:17,330 --> 01:05:19,623
- Are you still afraid?
- No.

656
01:05:19,791 --> 01:05:21,541
No, it's not that.

657
01:05:22,418 --> 01:05:24,169
Never mind.

658
01:05:26,422 --> 01:05:28,757
OK, should I make
a special dinner for two?

659
01:05:30,551 --> 01:05:33,971
- Go and watch TV. I'll cook.
- That's a little difficult.

660
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:58,662
Aren't you drinking too much?

661
01:05:59,288 --> 01:06:01,415
I'm celebrating.

662
01:06:01,582 --> 01:06:03,083
What?

663
01:06:03,251 --> 01:06:06,920
That in four days,

664
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:10,340
I will have the bandages removed
and I will see again.

665
01:06:11,884 --> 01:06:14,094
Everything will be all right, Julia.

666
01:06:15,430 --> 01:06:17,514
You know,

667
01:06:17,682 --> 01:06:21,852
if the operation doesn't work,
I couldn't complain.

668
01:06:22,603 --> 01:06:25,605
I have seen everything I wanted to see.

669
01:06:27,108 --> 01:06:30,444
What's the most beautiful thing
you've ever seen?

670
01:06:31,779 --> 01:06:33,572
Funny!

671
01:06:33,698 --> 01:06:36,158
How ironic that you ask me that.

672
01:06:36,325 --> 01:06:37,993
Why?

673
01:06:39,871 --> 01:06:44,499
Because I spent my whole life
looking for invisible planets.

674
01:06:44,667 --> 01:06:47,878
My eyes have seen amazing things.

675
01:06:48,588 --> 01:06:54,634
But nothing can compare
to the sky in the Sahara.

676
01:06:57,388 --> 01:07:00,140
That's where I met Isaac.

677
01:07:00,308 --> 01:07:05,562
We were on the same excursion
and we spent the whole night...

678
01:07:06,647 --> 01:07:09,232
...staring at the sky.

679
01:07:10,193 --> 01:07:14,613
I asked him, "Is that not the most
beautiful thing you've ever seen?"

680
01:07:15,364 --> 01:07:17,783
And he said, "Yes."

681
01:07:23,539 --> 01:07:25,832
When I turned my head,

682
01:07:26,000 --> 01:07:30,587
I realized that he'd been watching me
for a while and I got nervous.

683
01:07:31,714 --> 01:07:33,673
And I asked him...

684
01:07:36,344 --> 01:07:39,346
..."Why aren't you watching
the universe?"

685
01:07:40,014 --> 01:07:45,143
And he said,
"I don't have to look up to do it."

686
01:07:46,479 --> 01:07:49,815
"I can see the universe in your eyes."

687
01:07:52,026 --> 01:07:53,944
And what happened?

688
01:07:56,739 --> 01:07:58,657
I came close.

689
01:07:59,909 --> 01:08:01,535
I touched him.

690
01:08:02,537 --> 01:08:05,831
And I realized that he was nervous too.

691
01:08:06,374 --> 01:08:10,585
In that moment it was as if
we became one person.

692
01:08:10,753 --> 01:08:13,630
And I wanted to know
if he felt the same.

693
01:08:13,965 --> 01:08:16,049
What did he say?

694
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:18,760
Nothing.

695
01:08:20,429 --> 01:08:22,973
He replied with his gaze.

696
01:08:23,141 --> 01:08:24,766
Why?

697
01:08:24,934 --> 01:08:28,603
Why did he look at me that way? Why?

698
01:08:30,064 --> 01:08:34,067
- Do you prefer I hadn't done it?
- I don't know.

699
01:08:34,819 --> 01:08:40,240
When you had the affair with Sara,
I thought it was just an indiscretion,

700
01:08:40,408 --> 01:08:43,702
but I swear I don't know
what to think any more.

701
01:08:44,579 --> 01:08:46,788
I don't know what to think.

702
01:08:50,168 --> 01:08:52,919
Everything will be all right, Julia.

703
01:08:55,047 --> 01:08:56,923
You promise?

704
01:08:58,593 --> 01:09:00,594
I promise.

705
01:09:18,779 --> 01:09:20,405
No, I can't.

706
01:09:20,615 --> 01:09:22,657
I can't do it.

707
01:09:23,201 --> 01:09:25,285
It's not right.

708
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:33,460
- IvÃ¡n.
- Don't say anything.

709
01:09:33,669 --> 01:09:37,088
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be. Don't say anything.

710
01:09:37,256 --> 01:09:39,633
I'll call the hospital
and ask to be replaced.

711
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,551
Is that what you want?

712
01:09:43,262 --> 01:09:44,971
And you?

713
01:09:52,730 --> 01:09:55,899
OK, I'll come back tomorrow and...

714
01:09:56,776 --> 01:09:59,736
If not, just contact me on my pager.

715
01:11:30,244 --> 01:11:32,746
Help! Help!

716
01:11:35,082 --> 01:11:36,541
Help!

717
01:11:38,252 --> 01:11:42,422
Calm down!
I'm Blasco, the neighbor! Lia's father!

718
01:11:42,590 --> 01:11:45,050
Call the police, please!

719
01:11:46,135 --> 01:11:48,803
Calm down!
You need a drink.

720
01:11:48,971 --> 01:11:52,640
No, no.
Call the police, please.

721
01:11:52,767 --> 01:11:56,853
Why do you want to call the police?
To tell another one of your nightmares?

722
01:11:57,021 --> 01:12:01,149
- The last time they didn't believe you.
- No. There was someone by my bed.

723
01:12:01,317 --> 01:12:03,151
I swear, this time it's true.

724
01:12:03,277 --> 01:12:06,112
And what did he want?
To rape you?

725
01:12:07,615 --> 01:12:09,741
It's my daughter.
Don't be afraid.

726
01:12:09,909 --> 01:12:12,077
I told you not to sneak up on people!

727
01:12:12,244 --> 01:12:14,287
Go back to your bed!

728
01:12:14,705 --> 01:12:17,123
And close the door!

729
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:19,459
Mr Blasco...

730
01:12:20,628 --> 01:12:22,796
Can you call now, please?

731
01:12:26,133 --> 01:12:29,677
Of course, of course.
Don't worry.

732
01:12:31,889 --> 01:12:34,808
How strange.
There's no line.

733
01:12:37,353 --> 01:12:39,312
Calm down.

734
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,606
I'll get the mobile phone.

735
01:13:17,893 --> 01:13:23,189
The mobile is out of battery.
It will take a few minutes to charge.

736
01:13:25,276 --> 01:13:29,446
Sit down, sit down.

737
01:13:29,864 --> 01:13:31,823
Sit down.

738
01:13:32,700 --> 01:13:33,908
What do you say?

739
01:13:34,076 --> 01:13:39,914
Do you want something to drink
while we wait?

740
01:13:40,666 --> 01:13:44,002
- What do you say?
- Could I have a glass of water?

741
01:13:44,170 --> 01:13:49,132
- Water?
- Yes, my throat is a bit dry.

742
01:14:06,358 --> 01:14:09,527
Julia, where are you going?

743
01:14:10,404 --> 01:14:11,988
Hey!

744
01:14:12,740 --> 01:14:14,324
Hey!

745
01:14:14,783 --> 01:14:18,203
Madam!
Where are you, madam?

746
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:20,205
Madam!

747
01:14:21,540 --> 01:14:24,083
Please, pick up.

748
01:14:24,877 --> 01:14:26,544
IvÃ¡n.

749
01:14:26,837 --> 01:14:28,630
Pick up, please.

750
01:14:28,797 --> 01:14:29,839
Julia, what's wrong?

751
01:14:43,687 --> 01:14:45,188
- Julia!
- IvÃ¡n!

752
01:14:45,356 --> 01:14:48,733
- Let's go to your house.
- Not my house.

753
01:14:48,943 --> 01:14:51,236
- Julia, calm down.
- No, my house is not safe.

754
01:14:51,445 --> 01:14:54,072
Please. Take me to your place.

755
01:14:55,824 --> 01:14:57,492
OK.

756
01:14:57,618 --> 01:15:00,912
OK, thanks. Bye.

757
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:04,958
What did they say?

758
01:15:06,126 --> 01:15:09,254
Inspector Dimas
won't be on duty until seven.

759
01:15:10,381 --> 01:15:14,968
You should get some rest
and I'll go with you tomorrow morning.

760
01:15:15,135 --> 01:15:19,055
Julia, I won't let anyone hurt you.

761
01:15:20,808 --> 01:15:22,225
You can sleep in my bed.

762
01:15:22,393 --> 01:15:25,186
- And you?
- I have a mattress. I'll be right back.

763
01:15:25,312 --> 01:15:29,649
- No, no.
- I'll be right back. You're safe here.

764
01:15:29,817 --> 01:15:31,526
I'll be back in a minute.

765
01:15:47,334 --> 01:15:48,960
IvÃ¡n?

766
01:16:29,835 --> 01:16:31,544
- Who are you?
- I'm Lia.

767
01:16:31,712 --> 01:16:33,296
- Who are you?
- Lia Blasco.

768
01:16:33,464 --> 01:16:35,340
Don't get close.
How did you find me?

769
01:16:35,507 --> 01:16:38,801
- I followed you. I was Sara's friend.
- I said don't come close.

770
